sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K315008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Short version of pLacI promoter (56 bp) driving monomeric RFP with strong RBS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jes Testa

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091110
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a modified version of the LacI promoter that should bind LacI tighter than the original.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Robert Cool
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This promoter is a modified version of the LacI promoter

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K315021
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence is the wild type TetA gene which has been deoptimized from base pairs 144 to 290. This is a basic part that can be placed behind a promoter and produce the Tetracycline resistance protein. Being that this gene is deoptimized, we are hypothesizing that it will allow for less translational efficiency as compared to the wild type TetA (no data is available at this time to support or reject this hypothesis)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Danielle Wagner
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This TetA gene has been deoptimized from base pairs 144 to 290 using the online Optimizer program (http://genomes.urv.es/OPTIMIZER/) and was constructed using customized Oligo segments that were annealed and ligated into a pSB1A2 vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: During the design of this sequence, it was necessary to ensure that the deoptimized sequence did not contain BioBrick restriction sites and that the translational sequence was identical to that of the wild type gene
